<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-546-811  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 546 811.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 10 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: Que Software updates RightWriter. (Version 4.0 ofstyle and grammar checker) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Que Software (product introduction).andO;Product:   RightWriter 4.0 (Text editor) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionGrammar CritiquingStyle CritiquingWord processing softwareSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: Que Software Updates RightWriter CARMEL, INDIANA, U.S.A., 1990OCT 10 (NB) -- Que Software has unveiled Version 4.0 of RightWriter, itsDOS-based style and grammar checker.andM;The new release runs as a memory-resident program and is accessible using ahot key from six popular word processing programs, company publicist BethDouglass told Newsbytes.andP;  The hot key option works with WordPerfect,Microsoft Word, WordStar, Qandamp;A, Multimate Advantage, and Professional Write.andO;A PC with at least 512K bytes of memory is required.andM;The hot key feature is a major convenience for users, Douglass said.andP;  &quot;To theperson that uses it, it's a big deal.&quot;andM;Que has also added some 1,200 new grammatical rules to the package.andP;  Somecome from Strunk and White's &quot;The Elements of Style,&quot; a well-known book ongrammar and style.andP;  A copy of &quot;The Elements of Style&quot; is now packaged witheach copy of RightWriter, Douglass said.andM;RightWriter's parser, which analyzes sentences to make recommendations aboutstyle, has also been updated.andP;  With each release &quot;it gets closer and closerto natural language processing,&quot; Douglass said.andM;RightWriter 4.0 has a suggested retail price of US$99.andP;  Owners of previousversions can upgrade for US$25.andP;  Those who bought the package in the last 60days can upgrade free.andP;  More information is available by calling800-992-0244.andM;(Grant Buckler/19901008/Press Contact: Beth Douglass, Que Software,317-571-3489)</TEXT></DOC>